         <abstract>
            <p>After a long dry spell where lenders, servicers, and endcustomers were unwilling to try new ideas, it appears that a corner has been turned and innovation is becoming the new trend in mortgage tech. With looming political tailwinds, consumer preference shifts, and disruptive technologies like blockchain, the mortgage landscape will continue to be transformed in 2017 and beyond. Expect to see more innovation and consolidation as mortgage service companies place their bets for the coming "liftoff" in eMortgage.</p>
